                            ADDITIONAL TERMS & NOTICES
================================================================================

AGRICULTURAL USE DISCLAIMER:
This software is designed for agricultural monitoring and automation purposes.
While every effort has been made to ensure accuracy and reliability, users are
strongly advised to:

1. Verify all sensor readings and AI recommendations with professional 
   agricultural expertise before making critical farming decisions
2. Implement proper safety measures when using automated irrigation and 
   equipment control features
3. Regularly calibrate sensors and validate system outputs
4. Maintain backup monitoring systems for critical operations

DATA PRIVACY & COMPLIANCE:
Users are responsible for ensuring compliance with local data protection laws
(GDPR, CCPA, etc.) when collecting and processing agricultural and personal data.

THIRD-PARTY SERVICES:
This software integrates with various third-party services including:
- Supabase (Database & Authentication)
- IBM WatsonX AI (Recommendations)
- OpenWeatherMap (Weather Data)
- Bolt IoT Cloud (Device Control)
- Salesforce (Notifications)

Users must comply with the respective terms of service for each integrated
service and are responsible for any costs associated with their usage.

RESPONSIBLE USE:
This software is intended to promote sustainable and efficient agricultural
practices. Users are encouraged to use the system in ways that support
environmental conservation and responsible farming methods.

ATTRIBUTION (OPTIONAL):
While not required, attribution to the EcoBolt project is appreciated. This
helps support the open-source agricultural technology community.

COMMUNITY CONTRIBUTIONS:
Contributions to improve agricultural monitoring capabilities, add support for
new sensors, or enhance sustainability features are welcomed and encouraged.

